<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="73109" type="description">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="73109">Description</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="73109">
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="73109">Holotype male</emphasis>
. Total length 4.20 (habitus). Carapace: 2.15 long/2.20 wide, dark reddish-brown, round, slightly wider than long, clothed sparsely with serrated setae especially along the cervical furrow, cephalic region of prosoma flat with a pair of light stripes along the median line, numerous warts present, cervical and radial furrows distinct, dark longitudinal fovea slightly depressed (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="F7383544" captionText="Figure 2. Bassaniana birudis sp. nov., holotype male. A. Habitus in dorsal view; B. Ditto in ventral view; C. Ditto in frontal view; D. Ditto in lateral view; E. Eye area from above; F. Ditto from front; G. Femur; I. in prolateral view (arrow indicates two proximal protuberances). Scale bars in mm." figureDoi="10.3897/BDJ.9.e73109.figure2" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/575851" pageId="0" pageNumber="73109">2</figureCitation>
A and, C-E). Eyes: ALE 0.10, AME 0.06, PLE 0.14, PME 0.06, ALE-AME 0.17, AME-AME 0.30, PLE-PME 0.37, PME-PME 0.31, ALE-PLE 0.30, AME-PME 0.37, AER 0.58, PER 0.59, all eyes on the eye tubercle and lateral eye tubercles conspicuously developed, eight eyes in two rows, AER almost straight and PER recurved from above, AER strongly procurved and PER slightly procurved from front, PER longer than AER (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="F7383544" captionText="Figure 2. Bassaniana birudis sp. nov., holotype male. A. Habitus in dorsal view; B. Ditto in ventral view; C. Ditto in frontal view; D. Ditto in lateral view; E. Eye area from above; F. Ditto from front; G. Femur; I. in prolateral view (arrow indicates two proximal protuberances). Scale bars in mm." figureDoi="10.3897/BDJ.9.e73109.figure2" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/575851" pageId="0" pageNumber="73109">2</figureCitation>
E and, F). Chelicera; 0.62 long/0.35 wide, dark reddish-brown, light stripe and cross-shaped pattern on dorsal surface (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="F7383544" captionText="Figure 2. Bassaniana birudis sp. nov., holotype male. A. Habitus in dorsal view; B. Ditto in ventral view; C. Ditto in frontal view; D. Ditto in lateral view; E. Eye area from above; F. Ditto from front; G. Femur; I. in prolateral view (arrow indicates two proximal protuberances). Scale bars in mm." figureDoi="10.3897/BDJ.9.e73109.figure2" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/575851" pageId="0" pageNumber="73109">2</figureCitation>
C), no cheliceral teeth, fang very short. Endite: 0.45 long/0.18 wide, dark reddish-brown. Labium: 0.28 long/ 0.25 wide, dark reddish-brown. Sternum: 1.00 long/0.98 wide, mottled with dark and light reddish-brown, subcordate, clothed sparsely with long blackish-brown setae, pointed anteromedial margin protrudent, posterior end round and not protrudent between the coxae of leg IV (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="F7383544" captionText="Figure 2. Bassaniana birudis sp. nov., holotype male. A. Habitus in dorsal view; B. Ditto in ventral view; C. Ditto in frontal view; D. Ditto in lateral view; E. Eye area from above; F. Ditto from front; G. Femur; I. in prolateral view (arrow indicates two proximal protuberances). Scale bars in mm." figureDoi="10.3897/BDJ.9.e73109.figure2" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/575851" pageId="0" pageNumber="73109">2</figureCitation>
B). Legs: I 7.67 (2.40, 0.80, 1.67, 1.90, 0.90), II 6.84 (2.07, 0.80, 1.50, 1.65, 0.82), III 3.92 (0.87, 0.60, 0.85, 0.93, 0.67), IV 4.40 (1.00, 0.52, 0.90, 1.18, 0.80), ivory, stout and strongly developed, I and II mottled severely with dark reddish-brown, III and IV mottled weakly with dark reddish-brown (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="F7383544" captionText="Figure 2. Bassaniana birudis sp. nov., holotype male. A. Habitus in dorsal view; B. Ditto in ventral view; C. Ditto in frontal view; D. Ditto in lateral view; E. Eye area from above; F. Ditto from front; G. Femur; I. in prolateral view (arrow indicates two proximal protuberances). Scale bars in mm." figureDoi="10.3897/BDJ.9.e73109.figure2" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/575851" pageId="0" pageNumber="73109">2</figureCitation>
A and, D), femur with ventral stripe (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="F7383544" captionText="Figure 2. Bassaniana birudis sp. nov., holotype male. A. Habitus in dorsal view; B. Ditto in ventral view; C. Ditto in frontal view; D. Ditto in lateral view; E. Eye area from above; F. Ditto from front; G. Femur; I. in prolateral view (arrow indicates two proximal protuberances). Scale bars in mm." figureDoi="10.3897/BDJ.9.e73109.figure2" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/575851" pageId="0" pageNumber="73109">2</figureCitation>
B), femur I with two small rod-like proximal protuberances on prolateral surface (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="F7383544" captionText="Figure 2. Bassaniana birudis sp. nov., holotype male. A. Habitus in dorsal view; B. Ditto in ventral view; C. Ditto in frontal view; D. Ditto in lateral view; E. Eye area from above; F. Ditto from front; G. Femur; I. in prolateral view (arrow indicates two proximal protuberances). Scale bars in mm." figureDoi="10.3897/BDJ.9.e73109.figure2" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/575851" pageId="0" pageNumber="73109">2</figureCitation>
G), leg formula I-II-IV-III. Abdomen: 2.10 long/2.03 wide, ivory, flat and mottled with blackish-brown, yellowish-brown and reddish-brown, trapezoidal, slightly longer than wide, a pair of dark reddish-brown triangular markings paramedianly, numerous round or irregular pits on dorsal surface, clothed densely with semi-transparent clavate and serrated setae (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="F7383544" captionText="Figure 2. Bassaniana birudis sp. nov., holotype male. A. Habitus in dorsal view; B. Ditto in ventral view; C. Ditto in frontal view; D. Ditto in lateral view; E. Eye area from above; F. Ditto from front; G. Femur; I. in prolateral view (arrow indicates two proximal protuberances). Scale bars in mm." figureDoi="10.3897/BDJ.9.e73109.figure2" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/575851" pageId="0" pageNumber="73109">2</figureCitation>
A, C and, D; Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 3" captionStartId="F7481085" captionText="Figure 3. Bassaniana birudis sp. nov., holotype male. A. Palp in prolateral view; B. Ditto in ventral view; C. Ditto in retrolateral view; D. Ditto in dorsal view; E. Clavate seta; F. Serrated seta (E, embolus; RTA, retrolateral tibial apophysis; VTA, ventral tibial apophysis). Scale bars in mm." figureDoi="10.3897/BDJ.9.e73109.figure3" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/593313" pageId="0" pageNumber="73109">3</figureCitation>
E and, F). Palp: 2.57 (0.46, 0.41, 0.20, -, 0.70), bulb round and simple, left margin of tegulum slightly constricted, no tegulum apophysis, embolus thick with a pointed embolus tip straight rotating largely clockwise and close to the tegulum, thumb-like VTA large with a bent tip, thumb-like blunt RTA large (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 3" captionStartId="F7481085" captionText="Figure 3. Bassaniana birudis sp. nov., holotype male. A. Palp in prolateral view; B. Ditto in ventral view; C. Ditto in retrolateral view; D. Ditto in dorsal view; E. Clavate seta; F. Serrated seta (E, embolus; RTA, retrolateral tibial apophysis; VTA, ventral tibial apophysis). Scale bars in mm." figureDoi="10.3897/BDJ.9.e73109.figure3" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/593313" pageId="0" pageNumber="73109">3</figureCitation>
